  "body": "In some cases the state stored on a Keycard and one in the app may be inconsistent. \r\nFor example:\r\n- user may lock a Keycard during factory reset flow in onboarding\r\n- user may lock a Keycard while trying to log in\r\n- if user adds/removes wallet accounts for a keypair which is already migrated to a Keycard\r\n\r\nTo overcome such issues whenever user inserts a keycard and run any flow, if the inserted keycard is locked we need to update app's state accordingly. Another check should be done whenever user enters a pin we need to check if accounts stored on a Keycard match the state in the wallet section for keypair stored on that keycard, if not we need to update the Keycard accordingly.\r\n\r\nThose operations should be done silently, in the background, without any UI.\r\n\r\nNote:\r\nOne thing we cannot solve and will remain like that is, that we can have some dangling rows in `keypair` table for keycards we lost a track of. That may happen only in case if user resets a Keycard during onboarding flow. In that case new keycard unique number is generated and we don't know about previous one which is stored in db. Factory reset from the app (when user is logged in) is handled properly and keycard uid is updated properly in that case.",
